data.name: NS_E_WMP_CANNOT_BURN_NON_LOCAL_FILE
data.value: This file cannot be burned to a CD because it is not located on your computer.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_FILE_TYPE_CANNOT_BURN_TO_AUDIO_CD
data.value: It is not possible to burn this file type to an audio CD. Windows Media Player can burn the following file types to an audio CD: WMA, MP3, or WAV.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_FILE_DOES_NOT_FIT_ON_CD
data.value: This file is too large to fit on a disc.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_FILE_NO_DURATION
data.value: It is not possible to determine if this file can fit on a disc because Windows Media Player cannot detect the length of the file. Playing the file before burning might enable the Player to detect the file length.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_FAILED_TO_BURN
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered a problem while burning the file to the disc.

data.name: NS_E_FAILED_DOWNLOAD_ABORT_BURN
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot burn the audio CD because some items in the list that you chose to buy could not be downloaded from the online store.

data.name: NS_E_WMPCORE_DEVICE_DRIVERS_MISSING
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file. Try using Windows Update or Device Manager to update the device drivers for your audio and video cards. For information about using Windows Update or Device Manager, see Windows Help.

data.name: NS_E_WMPIM_USEROFFLINE
data.value: Windows Media Player has detected that you are not connected to the Internet. Connect to the Internet, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMPIM_USERCANCELED
data.value: The attempt to connect to the Internet was canceled.

data.name: NS_E_WMPIM_DIALUPFAILED
data.value: The attempt to connect to the Internet failed.

data.name: NS_E_WINSOCK_ERROR_STRING
data.value: Windows Media Player has encountered an unknown network error.

data.name: NS_E_WMPBR_NOLISTENER
data.value: No window is currently listening to Backup and Restore events.

data.name: NS_E_WMPBR_BACKUPCANCEL

data.name: NS_E_WMPBR_RESTORECANCEL
data.value: Your media usage rights were not restored because the restoration was canceled.

data.name: NS_E_WMPBR_ERRORWITHURL
data.value: An error occurred while backing up or restoring your media usage rights. A required web page cannot be displayed.

data.name: NS_E_WMPBR_NAMECOLLISION
data.value: Your media usage rights were not backed up because the backup was canceled.

data.name: NS_E_WMPBR_DRIVE_INVALID
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot restore your media usage rights from the specified location. Choose another location, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMPBR_BACKUPRESTOREFAILED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot backup or restore your media usage rights.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CONVERT_FILE_FAILED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot add the file to the library.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CONVERT_NO_RIGHTS_ERRORURL
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot add the file to the library because the content provider prohibits it. For assistance, contact the company that provided the file.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CONVERT_NO_RIGHTS_NOERRORURL
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot add the file to the library because the content provider prohibits it. For assistance, contact the company that provided the file.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CONVERT_FILE_CORRUPT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot add the file to the library. The file might not be valid.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CONVERT_PLUGIN_UNAVAILABLE_ERRORURL
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot add the file to the library. The plug-in required to add the file is not installed properly. For assistance, click Web Help to display the website of the company that provided the file.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CONVERT_PLUGIN_UNAVAILABLE_NOERRORURL
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot add the file to the library. The plug-in required to add the file is not installed properly. For assistance, contact the company that provided the file.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CONVERT_PLUGIN_UNKNOWN_FILE_OWNER
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot add the file to the library. The plug-in required to add the file is not installed properly. For assistance, contact the company that provided the file.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_DISC_COPY_PROTECT_OUTPUT_NS
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play this DVD. Try installing an updated driver for your video card or obtaining a newer video card.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_DISC_COPY_PROTECT_OUTPUT_FAILED
data.value: This DVD's resolution exceeds the maximum allowed by your component video outputs. Try reducing your screen resolution to 640 x 480, or turn off analog component outputs and use a VGA connection to your monitor.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_NO_SUBPICTURE_STREAM
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot display subtitles or highlights in DVD menus. Reinstall the DVD decoder or contact the DVD drive manufacturer to obtain an updated decoder.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_COPY_PROTECT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play this DVD because there is a problem with digital copy protection between your DVD drive, decoder, and video card. Try installing an updated driver for your video card.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_AUTHORING_PROBLEM
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the DVD. The disc was created in a manner that the Player does not support.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_INVALID_DISC_REGION
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the DVD because the disc prohibits playback in your region of the world. You must obtain a disc that is intended for your geographic region.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_COMPATIBLE_VIDEO_CARD
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the DVD because your video card does not support DVD playback.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_MACROVISION
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play this DVD because it is not possible to turn on analog copy protection on the output display. Try installing an updated driver for your video card.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_SYSTEM_DECODER_REGION
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the DVD because the region assigned to your DVD drive does not match the region assigned to your DVD decoder.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_DISC_DECODER_REGION
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the DVD because the disc prohibits playback in your region of the world. You must obtain a disc that is intended for your geographic region.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_NO_VIDEO_STREAM
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play DVD video. You might need to adjust your Windows display settings. Open display settings in Control Panel, and then try lowering your screen resolution and color quality settings.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_NO_AUDIO_STREAM
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play DVD audio. Verify that your sound card is set up correctly, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_GRAPH_BUILDING
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play DVD video. Close any open files and quit any other programs, and then try again. If the problem persists, restart your computer.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_NO_DECODER
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the DVD because a compatible DVD decoder is not installed on your computer.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_PARENTAL
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the scene because it has a parental rating higher than the rating that you are authorized to view.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_CANNOT_JUMP
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot skip to the requested location on the DVD.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_DEVICE_CONTENTION
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the DVD because it is currently in use by another program. Quit the other program that is using the DVD, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_NO_VIDEO_MEMORY
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play DVD video. You might need to adjust your Windows display settings. Open display settings in Control Panel, and then try lowering your screen resolution and color quality settings.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_CANNOT_COPY_PROTECTED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot rip the DVD because it is copy protected.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_REQUIRED_PROPERTY_NOT_SET
data.value: One of more of the required properties has not been set.

data.name: NS_E_DVD_INVALID_TITLE_CHAPTER
data.value: The specified title and/or chapter number does not exist on this DVD.

data.name: NS_E_NO_CD_BURNER
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot burn the files because the Player cannot find a burner. If the burner is connected properly, try using Windows Update to install the latest device driver.

data.name: NS_E_DEVICE_IS_NOT_READY
data.value: Windows Media Player does not detect storage media in the selected device. Insert storage media into the device, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot sync this file. The Player might not support the file type.

data.name: NS_E_NO_PDA
data.value: Windows Media Player does not detect a portable device. Connect your portable device, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_UNSPECIFIED_ERROR
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered an error while communicating with the device. The storage card on the device might be full, the device might be turned off, or the device might not allow playlists or folders to be created on it.

data.name: NS_E_MEMSTORAGE_BAD_DATA
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered an error while burning a CD.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_FAIL_SELECT_DEVICE
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered an error while communicating with a portable device or CD drive.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_FAIL_READ_WAVE_FILE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot open the WAV file.

data.name: NS_E_IMAPI_LOSSOFSTREAMING
data.value: Windows Media Player failed to burn all the files to the CD. Select a slower recording speed, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_DEVICE_FULL
data.value: There is not enough storage space on the portable device to complete this operation. Delete some unneeded files on the portable device, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_FAIL_LAUNCH_ROXIO_PLUGIN
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot burn the files. Verify that your burner is connected properly, and then try again. If the problem persists, reinstall the Player.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_DEVICE_FULL_IN_SESSION
data.value: Windows Media Player did not sync some files to the device because there is not enough storage space on the device.

data.name: NS_E_IMAPI_MEDIUM_INVALIDTYPE
data.value: The disc in the burner is not valid. Insert a blank disc into the burner, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_MANUALDEVICE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot perform the requested action because the device does not support sync.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_PARTNERSHIPNOTEXIST
data.value: To perform the requested action, you must first set up sync with the device.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_CANNOT_CREATE_ADDITIONAL_SYNC_RELATIONSHIP
data.value: You have already created sync partnerships with 16 devices. To create a new sync partnership, you must first end an existing partnership.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_NO_TRANSCODE_OF_DRM
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot sync the file because protected files cannot be converted to the required quality level or file format.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_TRANSCODECACHEFULL
data.value: The folder that stores converted files is full. Either empty the folder or increase its size, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_TOO_MANY_FILE_COLLISIONS
data.value: There are too many files with the same name in the folder on the device. Change the file name or sync to a different folder.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_CANNOT_TRANSCODE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot convert the file to the format required by the device.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_TOO_MANY_FILES_IN_DIRECTORY
data.value: You have reached the maximum number of files your device allows in a folder. If your device supports playback from subfolders, try creating subfolders on the device and storing some files in them.

data.name: NS_E_PROCESSINGSHOWSYNCWIZARD
data.value: Windows Media Player is already trying to start the Device Setup Wizard.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_TRANSCODE_NOT_PERMITTED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot convert this file format. If an updated version of the codec used to compress this file is available, install it and then try to sync the file again.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_INITIALIZINGDEVICES
data.value: Windows Media Player is busy setting up devices. Try again later.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_OBSOLETE_SP
data.value: Your device is using an outdated driver that is no longer supported by Windows Media Player.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_TITLE_COLLISION
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot sync the file because a file with the same name already exists on the device. Change the file name or try to sync the file to a different folder.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_DEVICESUPPORTDISABLED
data.value: Automatic and manual sync have been turned off temporarily. To sync to a device, restart Windows Media Player.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_NO_LONGER_AVAILABLE
data.value: This device is not available. Connect the device to the computer, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_ENCODER_NOT_RESPONDING
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot sync the file because an error occurred while converting the file to another quality level or format. If the problem persists, remove the file from the list of files to sync.

data.name: NS_E_PDA_CANNOT_SYNC_FROM_LOCATION
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot sync the file to your device. The file might be stored in a location that is not supported. Copy the file from its current location to your hard disk, add it to your library, and then try to sync the file again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_PROTOCOL_PROBLEM
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot open the specified URL. Verify that the Player is configured to use all available protocols, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_NO_DISK_SPACE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot perform the requested action because there is not enough storage space on your computer. Delete some unneeded files on your hard disk, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_LOGON_FAILURE
data.value: The server denied access to the file. Verify that you are using the correct user name and password.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CANNOT_FIND_FILE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot find the file. If you are trying to play, burn, or sync an item that is in your library, the item might point to a file that has been moved, renamed, or deleted.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_SERVER_INACCESSIBLE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot connect to the server. The server name might not be correct, the server might not be available, or your proxy settings might not be correct.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file. The Player might not support the file type or might not support the codec that was used to compress the file.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DSHOW_UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file. The Player might not support the file type or a required codec might not be installed on your computer.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_PLAYLIST_EXISTS
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot create the playlist because the name already exists. Type a different playlist name.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_NONMEDIA_FILES
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot delete the playlist because it contains items that are not digital media files. Any digital media files in the playlist were deleted.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_INVALID_ASX
data.value: The playlist cannot be opened because it is stored in a shared folder on another computer. If possible, move the playlist to the playlists folder on your computer.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_ALREADY_IN_USE
data.value: Windows Media Player is already in use. Stop playing any items, close all Player dialog boxes, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_IMAPI_FAILURE
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered an error while burning. Verify that the burner is connected properly and that the disc is clean and not damaged.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_WMDM_FAILURE
data.value: Windows Media Player has encountered an unknown error with your portable device. Reconnect your portable device, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CODEC_NEEDED_WITH_4CC
data.value: A codec is required to play this file. To determine if this codec is available to download from the web, click Web Help.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CODEC_NEEDED_WITH_FORMATTAG
data.value: An audio codec is needed to play this file. To determine if this codec is available to download from the web, click Web Help.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_MSSAP_NOT_AVAILABLE
data.value: To play the file, you must install the latest Windows service pack. To install the service pack from the Windows Update website, click Web Help.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_WMDM_INTERFACEDEAD
data.value: Windows Media Player no longer detects a portable device. Reconnect your portable device, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_WMDM_NOTCERTIFIED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot sync the file because the portable device does not support protected files.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_WMDM_LICENSE_NOTEXIST
data.value: This file does not have sync rights. If you obtained this file from an online store, go to the online store to get sync rights.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_WMDM_LICENSE_EXPIRED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot sync the file because the sync rights have expired. Go to the content provider's online store to get new sync rights.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_WMDM_BUSY
data.value: The portable device is already in use. Wait until the current task finishes or quit other programs that might be using the portable device, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_WMDM_NORIGHTS
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot sync the file because the content provider or device prohibits it. You might be able to resolve this problem by going to the content provider's online store to get sync rights.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_WMDM_INCORRECT_RIGHTS
data.value: The content provider has not granted you the right to sync this file. Go to the content provider's online store to get sync rights.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_IMAPI_GENERIC
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot burn the files to the CD. Verify that the disc is clean and not damaged. If necessary, select a slower recording speed or try a different brand of blank discs.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_IMAPI_DEVICE_NOTPRESENT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot burn the files. Verify that the burner is connected properly, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_IMAPI_DEVICE_BUSY
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot burn the files. Verify that the burner is connected properly and that the disc is clean and not damaged. If the burner is already in use, wait until the current task finishes or quit other programs that might be using the burner.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_IMAPI_LOSS_OF_STREAMING
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot burn the files to the CD.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_SERVER_UNAVAILABLE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file. The server might not be available or there might be a problem with your network or firewall settings.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_FILE_OPEN_FAILED
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered a problem while playing the file.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_VERIFY_ONLINE
data.value: Windows Media Player must connect to the Internet to verify the file's media usage rights. Connect to the Internet, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_SERVER_NOT_RESPONDING
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because a network error occurred. The server might not be available. Verify that you are connected to the network and that your proxy settings are correct.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_CORRUPT_BACKUP
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot restore your media usage rights because it could not find any backed up rights on your computer.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_LICENSE_SERVER_UNAVAILABLE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot download media usage rights because the server is not available (for example, the server might be busy or not online).

data.name: NS_E_WMP_NETWORK_FIREWALL
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file. A network firewall might be preventing the Player from opening the file by using the UDP transport protocol. If you typed a URL in the Open URL dialog box, try using a different transport protocol (for example, "http:").

data.name: NS_E_WMP_NO_REMOVABLE_MEDIA
data.value: Insert the removable media, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_PROXY_CONNECT_TIMEOUT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because the proxy server is not responding. The proxy server might be temporarily unavailable or your Player proxy settings might not be valid.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_NEED_UPGRADE
data.value: To play the file, you might need to install a later version of Windows Media Player. On the Help menu, click Check for Updates, and then follow the instructions.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_AUDIO_HW_PROBLEM
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because there is a problem with your sound device. There might not be a sound device installed on your computer, it might be in use by another program, or it might not be functioning properly.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_INVALID_PROTOCOL
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because the specified protocol is not supported. If you typed a URL in the Open URL dialog box, try using a different transport protocol (for example, "http:" or "rtsp:").

data.name: NS_E_WMP_INVALID_LIBRARY_ADD
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot add the file to the library because the file format is not supported.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_MMS_NOT_SUPPORTED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because the specified protocol is not supported. If you typed a URL in the Open URL dialog box, try using a different transport protocol (for example, "mms:").

data.name: NS_E_WMP_NO_PROTOCOLS_SELECTED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because there are no streaming protocols selected. Select one or more protocols, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_GOFULLSCREEN_FAILED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot switch to Full Screen. You might need to adjust your Windows display settings. Open display settings in Control Panel, and then try setting Hardware acceleration to Full.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_NETWORK_ERROR
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because a network error occurred. The server might not be available (for example, the server is busy or not online) or you might not be connected to the network.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CONNECT_TIMEOUT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because the server is not responding. Verify that you are connected to the network, and then try again later.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_MULTICAST_DISABLED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because the multicast protocol is not enabled. On the Tools menu, click Options, click the Network tab, and then select the Multicast check box.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_SERVER_DNS_TIMEOUT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because a network problem occurred. Verify that you are connected to the network, and then try again later.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_PROXY_NOT_FOUND
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because the network proxy server cannot be found. Verify that your proxy settings are correct, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_TAMPERED_CONTENT
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because it is corrupted.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_OUTOFMEMORY
data.value: Your computer is running low on memory. Quit other programs, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_AUDIO_CODEC_NOT_INSTALLED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play, burn, rip, or sync the file because a required audio codec is not installed on your computer.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_VIDEO_CODEC_NOT_INSTALLED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because the required video codec is not installed on your computer.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_IMAPI_DEVICE_INVALIDTYPE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot burn the files. If the burner is busy, wait for the current task to finish. If necessary, verify that the burner is connected properly and that you have installed the latest device driver.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_DRIVER_AUTH_FAILURE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the protected file because there is a problem with your sound device. Try installing a new device driver or use a different sound device.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_NETWORK_RESOURCE_FAILURE
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered a network error. Restart the Player.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_UPGRADE_APPLICATION
data.value: Windows Media Player is not installed properly. Reinstall the Player.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_UNKNOWN_ERROR
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered an unknown error.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_INVALID_KEY
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because the required codec is not valid.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CD_ANOTHER_USER
data.value: The CD drive is in use by another user. Wait for the task to complete, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_NEEDS_AUTHORIZATION
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play, sync, or burn the protected file because a problem occurred with the Windows Media Digital Rights Management (DRM) system. You might need to connect to the Internet to update your DRM components.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_BAD_DRIVER
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play the file because there might be a problem with your sound or video device. Try installing an updated device driver.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_ACCESS_DENIED
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot access the file. The file might be in use, you might not have access to the computer where the file is stored, or your proxy settings might not be correct.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_LICENSE_RESTRICTS
data.value: The content provider prohibits this action. Go to the content provider's online store to get new media usage rights.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_INVALID_REQUEST
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot perform the requested action at this time.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_CD_STASH_NO_SPACE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot burn the files because there is not enough free disk space to store the temporary files. Delete some unneeded files on your hard disk, and then try again.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_NEW_HARDWARE
data.value: Your media usage rights have become corrupted or are no longer valid. This might happen if you have replaced hardware components in your computer.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_INVALID_SIG
data.value: The required Windows Media Digital Rights Management (DRM) component cannot be validated. You might be able to resolve the problem by reinstalling the Player.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_CANNOT_RESTORE
data.value: You have exceeded your restore limit for the day. Try restoring your media usage rights tomorrow.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_BURN_DISC_OVERFLOW
data.value: Some files might not fit on the CD. The required space cannot be calculated accurately because some files might be missing duration information. To ensure the calculation is accurate, play the files that are missing duration information.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_GENERIC_LICENSE_FAILURE
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot verify the file's media usage rights. If you obtained this file from an online store, go to the online store to get the necessary rights.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_NO_SECURE_CLOCK
data.value: It is not possible to sync because this device's internal clock is not set correctly. To set the clock, select the option to set the device clock on the Privacy tab of the Options dialog box, connect to the Internet, and then sync the device again. For additional assistance, click Web Help.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_NO_RIGHTS
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot play, burn, rip, or sync the protected file because you do not have the appropriate rights.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_DRM_INDIV_FAILED
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered an error during upgrade.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_SERVER_NONEWCONNECTIONS
data.value: Windows Media Player cannot connect to the server because it is not accepting any new connections. This could be because it has reached its maximum connection limit. Please try again later.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_MULTIPLE_ERROR_IN_PLAYLIST
data.value: A number of queued files cannot be played. To find information about the problem, click the icon next to each file in the List pane.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_IMAPI2_ERASE_FAIL
data.value: Windows Media Player encountered an error while erasing the rewritable CD or DVD. Verify that the CD or DVD burner is connected properly and that the disc is clean and not damaged.

data.name: NS_E_WMP_IMAPI2_ERASE_DEVICE_BUSY

data.value: The function failed because a monitor returned an invalid Timing Status byte when the operating system used the DDC/CI Get Timing Report & Timing Message command to get a timing report from a monitor.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MCA_INVALID_CAPABILITIES_STRING
data.value: The monitor returned a DDC/CI capabilities string which did not comply with the ACCESS.bus 3.0, DDC/CI 1.1, or MCCS 2 Revision 1 specification.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MCA_INTERNAL_ERROR
data.value: An internal Monitor Configuration API error occurred.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_DDCCI_INVALID_MESSAGE_COMMAND
data.value: An operation failed because a DDC/CI message had an invalid value in its command field.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_DDCCI_INVALID_MESSAGE_LENGTH
data.value: An error occurred because the field length of a DDC/CI message contained an invalid value.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_DDCCI_INVALID_MESSAGE_CHECKSUM
data.value: An error occurred because the checksum field in a DDC/CI message did not match the message's computed checksum value. This error implies that the data was corrupted while it was being transmitted from a monitor to a computer.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_INVALID_PHYSICAL_MONITOR_HANDLE
data.value: This function failed because an invalid monitor handle was passed to it.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MONITOR_NO_LONGER_EXISTS
data.value: The operating system asynchronously destroyed the monitor which corresponds to this handle because the operating system's state changed. This error typically occurs because the monitor PDO associated with this handle was removed, the monitor PDO associated with this handle was stopped, or a display mode change occurred. A display mode change occurs when windows sends a WM_DISPLAYCHANGE windows message to applications.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_PMEA_INVALID_MONITOR
data.value: The HMONITOR no longer exists, is not attached to the desktop, or corresponds to a mirroring device.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_PMEA_INVALID_D3D_DEVICE
data.value: The Direct3D (D3D) device's GDI display device no longer exists, is not attached to the desktop, or is a mirroring display device.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_DDCCI_CURRENT_CURRENT_VALUE_GREATER_THAN_MAXIMUM_VALUE
data.value: A continuous VCP code's current value is greater than its maximum value. This error code indicates that a monitor returned an invalid value.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MCA_INVALID_VCP_VERSION
data.value: The monitor's VCP Version (0xDF) VCP code returned an invalid version value.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MCA_MONITOR_VIOLATES_MCCS_SPECIFICATION
data.value: The monitor does not comply with the MCCS specification it claims to support.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MCA_MCCS_VERSION_MISMATCH
data.value: The MCCS version in a monitor's mccs_ver capability does not match the MCCS version the monitor reports when the VCP Version (0xDF) VCP code is used.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MCA_UNSUPPORTED_MCCS_VERSION
data.value: The Monitor Configuration API only works with monitors which support the MCCS 1.0 specification, MCCS 2.0 specification or the MCCS 2.0 Revision 1 specification.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MCA_INVALID_TECHNOLOGY_TYPE_RETURNED
data.value: The monitor returned an invalid monitor technology type. CRT, Plasma and LCD (TFT) are examples of monitor technology types. This error implies that the monitor violated the MCCS 2.0 or MCCS 2.0 Revision 1 specification.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MCA_UNSUPPORTED_COLOR_TEMPERATURE
data.value: SetMonitorColorTemperature()'s caller passed a color temperature to it which the current monitor did not support. This error implies that the monitor violated the MCCS 2.0 or MCCS 2.0 Revision 1 specification.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_ONLY_CONSOLE_SESSION_SUPPORTED
data.value: This function can only be used if a program is running in the local console session. It cannot be used if the program is running on a remote desktop session or on a terminal server session.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_NO_DISPLAY_DEVICE_CORRESPONDS_TO_NAME
data.value: This function cannot find an actual GDI display device which corresponds to the specified GDI display device name.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_DISPLAY_DEVICE_NOT_ATTACHED_TO_DESKTOP
data.value: The function failed because the specified GDI display device was not attached to the Windows desktop.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_MIRRORING_DEVICES_NOT_SUPPORTED
data.value: This function does not support GDI mirroring display devices because GDI mirroring display devices do not have any physical monitors associated with them.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_INVALID_POINTER
data.value: The function failed because an invalid pointer parameter was passed to it. A pointer parameter is invalid if it is NULL, points to an invalid address, points to a kernel mode address, or is not correctly aligned.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_NO_MONITORS_CORRESPOND_TO_DISPLAY_DEVICE
data.value: The function failed because the specified GDI device did not have any monitors associated with it.

data.name: ERROR_GRAPHICS_PARAMETER_ARRAY_TOO_SMALL
data.value: An array passed to the function cannot hold all of the data that the function must copy into the array.

data.value: An internal error caused an operation to fail.
